snippet.textDisplay:
Here’s a tip that I learned from my baby and videos we watched on YouTube:
-if your baby is arching her back repeatedly it means either there’s one more burp that needs to be done, or a gas that needs to pass.
-if you lift her legs and move them in a cycling motion for 20 seconds, bend her legs and press down to her abs ... it helps release gas
- whatever you eat really does affect the baby ... I’m on a breastfeeding diet. I can’t eat greens or citrus fruits. It really does make your baby colicky
-you can tell that there’s air trapped by touching the sides of her belly and it feeling too hard.. sort of like stiff.
snippet.textOriginal:

snippet.textDisplay:
I know exactly what’s goin on But I’m not gonna say shit.
Colic isn’t real. Babies don’t just scream bloody murder for no reason. Something is hurting them if they are crying. Usually linked to gut health or if your baby is screaming, that blood curdling scream, check for encephalitis (brain swelling). Encephalitis is a pretty common reaction to their shots, it’s listed as a side effect in the package insert.
